SSSSTATIC(1)                    User Commands                   SSSSTATIC(1)

NAME
       sssstatic - A Simple Static Site Generator

SYNOPSIS
       sssstatic COMMAND [OPTIONS]

DESCRIPTION
       SSSStatic is a minimal static site generator that converts YAML
       configuration files into clean HTML websites. It provides a simple
       workflow for creating, building, and serving static sites with
       built-in themes and responsive design.

COMMANDS
       create new
              Create a new static site project. Prompts for project name
              and location, then generates the initial project structure
              with a _config.yml file.

       build
              Build the static site from the current directory's _config.yml
              file. Generates HTML output in the _site/ directory.

       serve [OPTIONS]
              Start a development server to preview the built site.

              -p, --port PORT
                     Specify the port to serve on (default: 8000)

              -d, --directory DIR
                     Specify the directory to serve (default: _site)

       dev [OPTIONS]
              Build the site and start development server in one command.
              Equivalent to running 'build' followed by 'serve'.

              -p, --port PORT
                     Specify the port to serve on (default: 8000)

              -d, --directory DIR
                     Specify the directory to serve (default: _site)

FILES
       _config.yml
              Main configuration file containing site metadata and content.
              Supports YAML format with nested data structures.

       _site/
              Output directory containing the generated static site files.

CONFIGURATION
       The _config.yml file supports the following structure:

   System Configuration (underscore-prefixed)
       _colorMode Color mode to use for styling. Options: "dark", "light".
              Default: "dark"

   Reserved Fields
       site_name
              The name of your site (used as page title and main heading)

   Content Structure
       Any other YAML structure becomes HTML content. Objects become
       sections with headings, lists become ordered lists, and URLs
       are automatically converted to clickable links.

THEMES
       Two built-in themes are available:

       dark   GitHub-inspired dark theme with syntax highlighting colors
              and modern styling (default)

       light  Clean, minimal light theme with professional appearance

       Set color mode using: _colorMode: "dark" or _colorMode: "light"

EXAMPLES
       Create a new project:
              $ sssstatic create new

       Build the current project:
              $ cd myproject
              $ sssstatic build

       Start development server:
              $ sssstatic serve --port 3000

       Build and serve in one command:
              $ sssstatic dev

       Serve custom directory:
              $ sssstatic serve --directory public

       Example _config.yml:
              site_name: "My Site"
              _colorMode: "dark"

              about:
                name: "John Doe"
                bio: "Developer"

              projects:
                - name: "Cool Project"
                  url: "https://github.com/user/project"
                  status: "active"

EXIT STATUS
       0      Success
       1      General error (missing config, invalid YAML, etc.)

AUTHOR
